rnal_base":"https://www.facebook.com/app_scoped_user_id/956354051097466/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":25729502,"talkid":100505,"etime_ts":"1486607152","thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/520414.html?thread=25729502#t25729502","above":25728478,"upictitle":"Douglas Long-Middleton: pic#125617633","article":"So do you refuse to give the Pats any credit? <br /><br />I see it as a bit of both. Yeah, the Falcons made some bad play calls, but the Pat's pass rush improved in the second half, and Tom Brady was... well, Tom Brady. <br /><br />It also solidifies Tom Brady as the greatest QB of all time. ","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"3 months ago","ctime":"February 9 2017, 02:14:32 UTC","parent":25727454,"massactions":0,"subject":"Re: Huh... no Super Bowl post.","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"https://www.facebook.com/app_scoped_user_id/956354051097466/","striked":null,"journaltype":"I","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/icons/facebook-16.png?v=29916?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"Douglas Long-Middleton","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":1,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"ext_3397776","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://www.livejournal.com/profile?userid=77094529&t=I","alias":0}],"etime":"February 9 2017, 02:25:52 UTC","dname":"Douglas Long-Middleton","ctime_ts":1486606472,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/124302622/73354478","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/520414.html?thread=25726942#t25726942","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/520414.html?thread=25726942#t25726942","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/520414.html?thread=25726942#t25726942","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"ext_2902334","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://twitter.com/ADragonDemands","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":25726942,"talkid":100495,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/520414.html?thread=25726942#t25726942","upictitle":"The Dragon Demands: pic#124302622","article":"A quick follow-up question to last post regarding \"Book of Swords\", ser:  you said that Gardner Dozois might only plausibly come to promote the anthology book at conventions in the northeast, given that he is based in Philadelphia.<br /><br />Well, my local scifi convention on Long Island is starting up again after a four year absence (hurricane damage) and we are setting up a robust track of Game of Thrones/ ASOIAF programming (8 hours of panels, 1 or 2 cast members).  <br /><br />We thought it might be a good idea to invite Gardner Dozois to help promote the anthology's recent announcement.  The problem is that we don't know what his professional point of contact is.  <br /><br />***I even asked Elio and Linda about this, and they said that they had no idea how to contact Mr. Dozois to ask if he can come (he actually came to our con once before back in the 1980's, though that was before my time).  <br /><br />So if you can help ser, even Elio didn't know this:  to what e-mail address should I send professional inquiries about scheduling a con appearance with Gardner Dozois?  (if you don't want to give out such info publicly, you could shoot Elio a message and he'd tell me).<br /><br />Also we've been trying to contact Anne Groell to ask if she'd like to come too, but everyone seems out of the office this week (We're having a whole panel on the World of Ice and Fire, she lives in New York, thought she might want to come to help promote it).  The contact Elio told me to e-mail at Random House is only sending me auto-replies, and the convention is in one month. <br /><br />Any help in contacting them would be a great help - though for all I know they're busy that week anyway.","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"3 months ago","ctime":"February 8 2017, 23:40:39 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"Gardner Dozois and Anne Groell","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://twitter.com/ADragonDemands","striked":null,"journaltype":"I","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/icons/twitter-16.png?v=29916?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"ADragonDemands","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":1,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"ext_2902334","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://www.livejournal.com/profile?userid=73354478&t=I","alias":0}],"dname":"ADragonDemands","ctime_ts":1486597239,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/91237832/7059164","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/520414.html?thread=25744094#t25744094","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/520414.html?thread=25744094#t25744094","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/520414.html?thread=25744094#t25744094","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"grrm","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":25744094,"talkid":100562,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/520414.html?thread=25744094#t25744094","above":25726942,"upictitle":"George R.R. Martin: Spain","article":"I've passed on your query to Gardner and Anne.","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"2 months ago","ctime":"February 14 2017, 20:53:29 UTC","parent":25726942,"massactions":0,"subject":"Re: Gardner Dozois and Anne Groell","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"grrm","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"grrm","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"grrm","ctime_ts":1487105609,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/124302622/73354478","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/520414.html?thread=25747934#t25747934","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/520414.html?thread=25747934#t25747934","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/520414.html?thread=25747934#t25747934","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"ext_2902334","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://twitter.com/ADragonDemands","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":25747934,"talkid":100577,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/520414.html?thread=25747934#t25747934","above":25744094,"upictitle":"The Dragon Demands: pic#124302622","article":"Whoa, thanks!","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"2 months ago","ctime":"February 15 2017, 04:55:57 UTC","parent":25744094,"massactions":0,"subject":"Re: Gardner Dozois and Anne Groell","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://twitter.com/ADragonDemands","striked":null,"journaltype":"I","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/icons/twitter-16.png?v=29916?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"ADragonDemands","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":1,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"ext_2902334","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://www.livejournal.com/profile?userid=73354478&t=I","alias":0}],"dname":"ADragonDemands","ctime_ts":1487134557,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/520414.html?thread=25727198#t25727198","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/520414.html?thread=25727198#t25727198","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/520414.html?thread=25727198#t25727198","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"ext_4010398","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"https://plus.google.com/116730841571516183122","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":25727198,"talkid":100496,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/520414.html?thread=25727198#t25727198","upictitle":"Kevin Moore: pic#0","article":"Dear Mr. Martin,<br /><br />I post this not to ask for information or a reply - or even in hopes that it will make it through the screening process to appear online. Instead, I'm writing to provide information, in light of your statements about avoiding fan forums. This is no doubt an excellent idea but there's one issue I hope you know about as it could affect posterity's view of the finished work. The \"Murder of Jon Arryn\" is a resolved mystery worthy of Dame Agatha herself and superior to all but a handful of her greatest works. But there are two other mysteries that the HBO show seems to think are also resolved. The information I want to give you is that a massive portion of the fandom is not convinced and the debate rages on endlessly. I'm hoping that this is your intention, but if you're not aware of the controversies I'm writing to give you a heads up. The big one is \"The Murder of Joffrey Baratheon\". Everyone has gone over and over all the pertinent chapters with their microscopes and the version shown on HBO simply isn't provable anywhere near beyond a shadow of a doubt. The other one is \"Cat and the Catspaw\". Over a decade ago you publicly said that this would be settled in A Storm of Swords, but I'm here to tell you that it most certainly is not! Even Mance and his bag of silver are suspected! If it is Joff, I think literature teachers in 200 years would thank you greatly if you confirmed it before the end of the series. Thanks to you or your minion for reading this. I consider ASOIAF to be arguably the greatest work of fiction ever written and I wait with supreme patience for the next installment.","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"3 months ago","ctime":"February 9 2017, 00:07:54 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"quick private message","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"https://plus.google.com/116730841571516183122","striked":null,"journaltype":"I","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/icons/google-16.png?v=29916?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"Kevin Moore","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":1,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"ext_4010398","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://www.livejournal.com/profile?userid=81081079&t=I","alias":0}],"dname":"Kevin Moore","ctime_ts":1486598874,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/91237832/7059164","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/520414.html?thread=25727710#t25727710","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/520414.html?thread=25727710#t25727710","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/520414.html?thread=25727710#t25727710","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"grrm","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":25727710,"talkid":100498,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/520414.html?thread=25727710#t25727710","above":25727198,"upictitle":"George R.R. Martin: Spain","article":"This is a Wild Cards topic.  ","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"3 months ago","ctime":"February 9 2017, 00:17:37 UTC","parent":25727198,"massactions":0,"subject":"Re: quick private message","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"n